  "prompt": "What does the GDP per capita represent?",
  "response": "GDP per capita represents the total economic output (Gross Domestic Product) of a country divided by its total population. It is a measure of the average economic productivity and standard of living for individuals in a country. Specifically, it shows:\n\n1. Average economic output per person\n2. Rough indication of a country's economic prosperity\n3. Potential purchasing power of an average citizen\n4. A basic metric for comparing economic performance between countries\n\nThe calculation is typically done by dividing a country's total GDP by its total population, usually measured annually and expressed in current local currency or U.S. dollars.",
